Python Development Domain - Slab 1 [Beginner]
This directory contains the completed beginner-level tasks for the QSkill Python Development Internship. These projects demonstrate core competencies in data handling, predictive modeling, and mathematical application development.

🚀 Projects Overview
1. Data Analysis & Visualization
Objective: Extract actionable insights from raw data using statistical analysis and graphical representations.

Core Logic: Utilized Pandas for data manipulation and Seaborn/Matplotlib for visualization.

Key Achievement: Developed a script that automatically generates correlation heatmaps and distribution charts to identify data trends.

2. House Price Prediction Model
Objective: Predict real estate pricing based on physical attributes using supervised learning.

Core Logic: Implemented a Linear Regression algorithm using Scikit-Learn.

Key Achievement: Successfully trained a model with high predictive accuracy (R-squared score) and visualized the variance between actual and predicted values.

3. Matrix Operations Tool
Objective: Build a command-line interface (CLI) for advanced linear algebra operations.

Core Logic: Leveraged NumPy for high-performance array computations.

Key Achievement: Created an interactive menu-driven system that handles transposition, determinants, and matrix arithmetic with error handling for dimension mismatches.

🛠️ Technical Skills Demonstrated
Data Science Stack: NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-Learn.

Visualization: Matplotlib, Seaborn.

Programming: CLI development, Object-Oriented concepts, and error handling.

Version Control: Git/GitHub for professional code management.

💻 Installation & Execution
To run any of the tasks locally, follow these steps:

Install Dependencies:

Bash
pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn matplotlib seaborn
Navigate to the Task Folder:

Bash
cd Task_1  # or Task_2, Task_3
Execute the Script:

Bash
python <filename>.py
